    "In an attempt to provide a broader and at the same time a more concise picture of the necessary actions towards sustainability, Sachs et al.",
    "9 presented the Six Transformations as a means to operationalize the SDGs.",
    "They practically grouped the 17 goals into six key areas of transformation that societies need to undertake for sustainable development.",
    "These are: 1.",
    "Education, Gender, and Inequality, recognizing that sustainable development requires a foundation of educated citizens, with equal opportunities for all genders and marginalized groups; 2."
